{"title_page": "John de Ludlow", "text_new": "{{other people|John Ludlow}}\n'''John de Ludlow''' (also '''Ludlaw''') was an [[England|English]] medieval university [[Chancellor (education)|chancellor]].<ref name=\"hibbert\">{{cite book|title=[[The Encyclopaedia of Oxford]] |publisher=[[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]]|chapter=Appendix 5: Chancellors of the University |year=1988 |pages=521\u2013522 |isbn=0-333-39917-X| editor-last=Hibbert|editor-first=Christopher|editor-link=Christopher Hibbert}}</ref>\n\nIn 1290, John de Ludlow was [[Chancellor of the University of Oxford|Chancellor]] of the [[University of Oxford]], resigning in the same year.<ref name=\"wood\">{{cite book| title=The History and Antiquities of the Colleges and Halls in the University of Oxford | via=[[Internet Archive]] | first=Anthony | last=Wood| url=https://archive.org/details/appendixtohistor00wood | chapter=Fasti Oxonienses | year=1790 | page=[https://archive.org/details/appendixtohistor00wood/page/15 15] }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ludlow]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Chancellor of the University of Oxford]]\n| years=1290\n| before=[[William de Kingescote]]\n| after=[[John of Monmouth (bishop)|John of Monmouth]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Chancellors of the University of Oxford}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ludlow, John de}}\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:Year of death unknown]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:13th-century English people]]\n[[Category:English male writers]]\n\n\n{{UOxford-stub}}\n{{England-academic-administrator-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{otherpeople|John Ludlow}}\n'''John de Ludlow''' (also '''Ludlaw''') was an [[England|English]] medieval university [[Chancellor (education)|chancellor]].<ref name=\"hibbert\">{{cite book|title=[[The Encyclopaedia of Oxford]] |publisher=[[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]]|chapter=Appendix 5: Chancellors of the University |year=1988 |pages=521\u2013522 |isbn=0-333-39917-X| editor-last=Hibbert|editor-first=Christopher|editor-link=Christopher Hibbert}}</ref>\n\nIn 1290, John de Ludlow was [[Chancellor of the University of Oxford|Chancellor]] of the [[University of Oxford]], resigning in the same year.<ref name=\"wood\">{{cite book| title=The History and Antiquities of the Colleges and Halls in the University of Oxford | via=[[Internet Archive]] | first=Anthony | last=Wood| url=https://archive.org/details/appendixtohistor00wood | chapter=Fasti Oxonienses | year=1790 | page=[https://archive.org/details/appendixtohistor00wood/page/15 15] }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ludlow]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Chancellor of the University of Oxford]]\n| years=1290\n| before=[[William de Kingescote]]\n| after=[[John of Monmouth (bishop)|John of Monmouth]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Chancellors of the University of Oxford}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ludlow, John de}}\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:Year of death unknown]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:13th-century English people]]\n[[Category:English male writers]]\n\n\n{{UOxford-stub}}\n{{England-academic-administrator-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_de_Ludlow"}
{"title_page": "Surendranath Centenary School", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{More citations needed|date=September 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name        = Surendranath Centenary School\n| lgo        = [[File:SNCS logo.JPG|center|Logo]]\n| established = 1988\n| type        = [[Independent school]]\n| head_name   = Principal\n| head        = Mr. Uma bhaiya\n| students    = 3200+\n| motto       = Nothing Beyond\n| free_label  =\n| affiliation = [[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]]\n| classes     = U.K.G. - Xll\n| free        =\n| location    = H B Road Dipatoli-834009\n| city        = [[Ranchi]]\n| state       = [[Jharkhand]]\n| country     = [[India]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|23.3843872|N|85.3680393|E|region:LK_type:edu|display=inline}}\n| pushpin_map = India Jharkhand#India\n\n==History==\nThe school is affiliated to the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]. Its name commemorates [[Surendranath Banerjee]], a leader of India's independence movement and co-founder of the National Council of Education in [[Calcutta]].\n\n[[File:Surendranath Centenary School.jpg|left|thumb]]\nThe school has two buildings. The Ranadeb Chaudhuri Block is used for primary education from Upper Kindergarten (UKG) to year V. The senior wing for years VI to XII is on four floors and includes science laboratories and computer labs.\n\nStudents are assigned to one of four houses.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Education in India]]\n*[[Literacy in India]]\n*[[List of schools in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal bar|India|School|Education}}\n\n[[Category:Primary schools in India]]\n[[Category:High schools and secondary schools in Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Private schools in Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Schools in Ranchi]]\n[[Category:Schools affiliated to CBSE]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1988]]\n[[Category:1988 establishments in India]]\n\n\n{{Jharkhand-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{More citations needed|date=September 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name        = Surendranath Centenary School\n| logo        = [[File:SNCS logo.JPG|center|Logo]]\n| established = 1988\n| type        = [[Independent school]]\n| head_name   = Principal\n| head        = Mrs. Samita Sinha\n| students    = 3200+\n| motto       = Nothing Beyond\n| free_label  =\n| affiliation = [[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]]\n| classes     = U.K.G. - Xll\n| free        =\n| location    = H B Road Dipatoli-834009\n| city        = [[Ranchi]]\n| state       = [[Jharkhand]]\n| country     = [[India]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|23.3843872|N|85.3680393|E|region:LK_type:edu|display=inline}}\n| pushpin_map = India Jharkhand#India\n| website     = http://www.scsranchi.com/\n}}\n\n'''Surendranath Centenary School''' is an [[English-medium education|English-medium]] school in [[Ranchi]], [[India]] established in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|title=About the school|url=http://www.scsranchi.com/abot/index.htm|website=Surendranath Centenary School|accessdate=30 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe school is affiliated to the [[Central Board of Secondary Education]]. Its name commemorates [[Surendranath Banerjee]], a leader of India's independence movement and co-founder of the National Council of Education in [[Calcutta]].\n\n[[File:Surendranath Centenary School.jpg|left|thumb]]\nThe school has two buildings. The Ranadeb Chaudhuri Block is used for primary education from Upper Kindergarten (UKG) to year V. The senior wing for years VI to XII is on four floors and includes science laboratories and computer labs.\n\nStudents are assigned to one of four houses.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Education in India]]\n*[[Literacy in India]]\n*[[List of schools in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal bar|India|School|Education}}\n\n[[Category:Primary schools in India]]\n[[Category:High schools and secondary schools in Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Private schools in Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Schools in Ranchi]]\n[[Category:Schools affiliated to CBSE]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1988]]\n[[Category:1988 establishments in India]]\n\n\n{{Jharkhand-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2409:4064:2386:8fe2:4859:86e1:9479:3398", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surendranath_Centenary_School"}
